solution: class Solution {
public:
    int trailingZeroes(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n > 0) {
            n /= 5;
            count += n;
        }
        return count;
    }
};
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Counts the number of factors of 5 in n! by repeatedly dividing n by 5 and summing the quotients. This directly gives the number of trailing zeroes since each zero is produced by a pair of 2 and 5, and 5s are the limiting factor.

